modules.description: Provides functions to load, manage, and query a collection of root certificate authorities. Works with X509 certificate structures and PEM-encoded data. Used to configure secure TLS connections by supplying trusted anchors to the ocaml-tls library.

Detects root CAs in the system's trust store and returns PEM-encoded certificates. Constructs an authenticator with optional CRLs and hash restrictions for TLS client configuration. Used to establish secure, verified TLS connections by validating server certificates against trusted roots.
